posts.cooked: We are attempting to image some Orange pi 5s with photonvision, but the pi’s aren’t booting. I’ve tried all the troubleshooting in the docs, imaging with different tools(balena etcher, raspberry pi imaging tool, etc.) but nothing works. Wondering if there is something I’m doing wrong, or if there’s something else I can try.

posts.name: Alex
posts.cooked: What do u mean by not booting? No power? Can’t ssh? Can’t get to web ui?

Power, but the os does not boot. When plugged into a display it just displays the orange pi logo which, after reading some documentation, means it cannot find a bootable drive. I am also sure that I am using the correct image

posts.name: Sam
posts.cooked:
Can u redownload the image that corresponds to your model of opi and try reflashing it?

(I made a typo)
I can do that once I get back to our shop tomorrow, I am also going to try with a brand new microsd as the one I tried today did not work at all

posts.name: Anand Rajamani
posts.cooked:
What model of orange pi specifically? What power supply are you using?

Most common issues are the wrong Orange Pi 5 image being used, or a weak power supply.
Just the base 5 model, and we’re powering it using an anker power bank that we know is enough

posts.name: Anand Rajamani
posts.cooked: Good choice! Regular Opi is the way to go. Make sure you’re using the regular image and not the image for the Plus or Pro or whatever other versions they have now. Also, try a 3A+ 5V wall supply. Power banks can be wonky sometimes. And make sure you’re using a good cable, preferably one that you know can support USB C PD. Not because the Opi 5 uses PD, but because that indicates that it can carry a decent bit of current.

UPDATE

the issue is solved! I used a brand new sd card and it worked. The previous sd cards were class 10 cards, which are inconsistent with orange pis. We have switched to A2 cards and it works perfectly

posts.name: Yishai Levy
posts.cooked: Do you think it should work with an A1 SD card? We’re having a similar problem with them.
I should specify further in the solution that we are using uhs3 speed class, as that was the main issue. I think uhs3 a1 will work
